README
This tool generates 2D grids.

INSTRUCTIONS:

To Build:
    Ubuntu:
    > ./setup_ubuntu.sh

    Arch:
    > ./setup_arch.sh

    Otherwise:
    - Pull repository: https://github.com/mseryn/stl_tools.git
    - From stl_tools/, move stl_tools/stl_tools/ to diffraction_grating_generator/

To Run:
> ./make_grating.sh

Manual run:
> ./src/difraction_grating_generator <Number of Rows> <Number of Columns> <Slit Pitch> <Slit Length>

NOTES:
- Output files have relative dimensions - no units are implicit



AUTHOR:
Melanie Cornelius (nee Dooley)
Built for the Illinois Institute of Technology Interprofessional Project:
Developing an Antimatter Gravity Interferometer

CURRENT OUTPUT FORMATS:
.stl

FUTURE OUTPUT FORMATS:
L-Edit cells

CURRENT GEOMETRIES:
Columnar grid

FUTURE GEOMETRIES:
Psudo-random
Ashlar

